**`craigslist_bike_scraper.py`** is a precision tool for scraping _Santa Cruz bikes_ (specifically `bronson`, `5010`, and `nomad` models) from Craigslist listings around the SF Bay Area.

Think of it as your personal bike scout. Tireless. Unemotional. Fluent in HTML.  
And when it finds something tasty, it drops it directly in your Discord like this:  
ðŸ“¤ `Santa Cruz Bronson, Large â€” $3200 (Watsonville)`

---

## ðŸ§  Features

- ðŸ•¸ **Real-time Craigslist scraping** via headless Chromium & Selenium
- ðŸ§½ **Smart attribute parsing** (model, size, year, etc.) using BeautifulSoup
- â³ **Waits for JavaScript-rendered content** before parsing
- â— **Keyword de-spamming**: Ignores those icky keyword-stuffed blocks
- ðŸ§  **False negative reducers**: Parses even when Craigslist uses funky formatting
- ðŸ“¢ **Automatic Discord alerts** via webhook
- ðŸ¤– **Logs everything** it finds, skips, or posts
- ðŸ§¯ **Fails gracefully** on slow pages, missing elements, or Razor scooters

